<h2 id="the-rights-of-eu-citizens-when-arriving-in-the-uk-after-the-uk-leaves-the-eu-to-access-social-housing-and-homelessness-assistance">The rights of <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> citizens when arriving in the UK after the UK leaves the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> to access social housing and homelessness assistance</h2>

<p>In a no deal Brexit, after the UK leaves the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> on 31 October 2019,  <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> citizens arriving between 31 October 2019 until 31 December 2020 will still be able to live, study, work and access benefits and services as they do now, for a temporary period. This includes access to social housing, including supported housing, and homelessness assistance.</p>

<p>Those wishing to stay beyond December 2020 will need to apply for <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/no-deal-immigration-arrangements-for-eu-citizens-moving-to-the-uk-after-brexit">European Temporary Leave to Remain</a> which will last 36 months, running from the date the leave is granted. The right to access social housing, supported housing and homelessness assistance will remain unchanged for the duration of this leave.</p>

<p>The UK government will introduce a new points-based immigration system from 2021.</p>

<h2 id="what-will-change-for-local-authorities">What will change for local authorities?</h2>

<p>Applications for social housing and homelessness assistance in England are managed by local authorities. The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government is working with local authorities to ensure they are prepared for any changes to <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> citizens’ eligibility to access social housing and homelessness assistance after the UK has left the <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr>.</p>

<p>Further information on how to contact a local authority about housing in England is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/council-housing">gov.uk</a>.
Housing is a devolved government function. You can access further information on social housing in Wales at <a rel="external" href="https://gov.wales/topics/housing-and-regeneration/?lang=en">gov.wales</a>, in Northern Ireland at <a rel="external" href="https://www.nidirect.gov.uk/information-and-services/property-and-housing/social-housing">nidirect.gov</a>, and in Scotland at <a rel="external" href="https://www.mygov.scot/apply-for-housing/">mygov.scot</a>.</p>

